(5, 'Cybersecurity', 450, 'Dr. Emily Smith', '2024-09-25', '16 Weeks', 'Comprehensive course on security protocols.', 'This course provides a comprehensive introduction to Cybersecurity, covering the essential concepts, tools, and techniques used to protect systems, networks, and data from cyber threats.<br> You will learn key cybersecurity topics, including network security, cryptography, ethical hacking, vulnerability assessment, and incident response.<br> The course also explores risk management, security policies, and compliance frameworks that help organizations safeguard their digital assets.<br>  The course is structured into modules that start with the fundamentals of cybersecurity, including basic security principles and common attack vectors, and then progress into more advanced topics like penetration testing, malware analysis, and defense strategies.<br> By the end of the course, you will be capable of identifying potential security vulnerabilities, implementing protective measures, and responding to security incidents.<br>  This course is ideal for beginners and IT professionals looking to strengthen their knowledge of cybersecurity and protect against real-world cyber threats.<br>', 'cybersecurity.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/shQEXpUwaIY', 'Cybersecurity'),
