(13, 'Basics of C++', 30, 'Osama Elzero', '2024-09-28', '4 Weeks', 'Learn the basics of C++ programming, including syntax, loops, functions, and object-oriented programming.', 'This course provides a comprehensive introduction to Basics of C++, covering the essential concepts and programming techniques needed to develop robust and efficient applications using C++.<br> You will learn key C++ topics, including syntax, data types, control structures, functions, and object-oriented programming principles.<br> The course also explores memory management, file handling, and basic use of the C++ Standard Library.<br>  The course is structured into modules that start with fundamental programming concepts, including basic syntax and data types, and progress into more advanced topics like classes and objects, inheritance, polymorphism, and operator overloading.<br> By the end of the course, you will have hands-on experience writing C++ programs, debugging, and understanding core programming practices and concepts.<br>  This course is ideal for beginners and those new to C++, as well as developers looking to strengthen their understanding of foundational programming concepts and enhance their skills in C++ development.<br>', 'Basics_of_C++.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/MNeX4EGtR5Y', 'Programming'),
(14, 'Advanced JavaScript', 300, 'Dr. Alice Williams', '2024-10-15', '4 Weeks', 'Deep dive into advanced JavaScript concepts including ES6, asynchronous programming, and more.', 'This course provides a comprehensive exploration of Advanced JavaScript, covering sophisticated techniques and concepts to enhance your JavaScript programming skills and build more dynamic, efficient, and scalable web applications.<br> You will learn advanced JavaScript topics, including asynchronous programming, advanced functions, and modern JavaScript features introduced in ES6 and beyond.<br> The course also delves into JavaScript frameworks and libraries, such as React, Angular, and Vue.js, and explores advanced topics like performance optimization and design patterns.<br>  The course is structured into modules that begin with advanced JavaScript syntax and concepts, such as closures, promises, and async/await, and progress into more complex topics like functional programming, state management, and building complex web applications.<br> By the end of the course, you will have hands-on experience with advanced JavaScript techniques, understanding of modern JavaScript frameworks, and skills to develop robust and scalable web applications.<br>  This course is ideal for experienced JavaScript developers looking to deepen their knowledge and expertise, as well as those interested in mastering advanced JavaScript techniques and building sophisticated web applications.<br>', 'Advanced_JavaScript.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/lkIFF4maKMU', 'Web Development'),
