(18, 'Natural Language Processing (NLP)', 550, 'Dr. Michael Johnson', '2024-10-03', '6 Weeks', 'Explore techniques and tools for processing and analyzing human language data.', 'This course provides a comprehensive introduction to Natural Language Processing (NLP), focusing on techniques and tools for analyzing and understanding human language using computational methods.<br> You will learn key NLP topics, including text processing, sentiment analysis, named entity recognition, machine translation, and language generation.<br> The course also explores advanced topics such as word embeddings, transformer models like BERT and GPT, and techniques for building conversational agents and chatbots.<br>  The course is structured into modules that start with the fundamentals of NLP, including text preprocessing and basic algorithms, and progress into more advanced topics like deep learning for NLP, handling large-scale text data, and implementing state-of-the-art NLP models.<br> By the end of the course, you will have hands-on experience with NLP tasks and tools, including building and training models for various natural language understanding and generation tasks, and applying these techniques to real-world problems.<br>  This course is ideal for beginners and professionals looking to develop their skills in NLP and apply machine learning techniques to analyze and interpret human language.<br>', 'NLP.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/CMrHM8a3hqw', 'AI'),
