(20, 'Java Programming for Beginners', 250, 'Dr. Linda White', '2024-10-08', '4 Weeks', 'Introduction to Java programming including basic syntax, control flow, and object-oriented principles.', 'This course provides a comprehensive introduction to Java Programming for Beginners, focusing on the foundational concepts and techniques needed to start programming with Java.<br> You will learn key Java topics, including syntax, data types, control structures, object-oriented programming principles, and basic application development.<br> The course also covers essential concepts such as classes, objects, methods, and exception handling, and introduces basic Java development tools and practices.<br>  The course is structured into modules that begin with the basics of Java programming, including understanding the Java programming environment, and progress into more advanced topics like object-oriented programming, working with libraries and APIs, and debugging techniques.<br> By the end of the course, you will have hands-on experience writing, testing, and debugging Java programs, as well as understanding core programming practices and Java concepts.<br>  This course is ideal for beginners with little or no prior programming experience, and those looking to build a strong foundation in Java programming to advance their software development skills.<br>', 'Java_Programming_Beginners.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/mAtkPQO1FcA', 'Programming'),
