(23, 'AI Ethics and Policy', 450, 'Dr. Helen Adams', '2024-10-05', '4 Weeks', 'Understand ethical considerations and policies related to AI.', 'This course provides a comprehensive introduction to AI Ethics and Policy, focusing on the ethical considerations and policy frameworks related to the development and deployment of artificial intelligence technologies.<br> You will learn key topics, including the ethical implications of AI, bias and fairness in AI systems, privacy concerns, and the impact of AI on society.<br> The course also explores regulatory frameworks, policy development, and strategies for responsible AI governance and implementation.<br>  The course is structured into modules that start with foundational ethical principles and issues in AI, including understanding the impact of AI on individuals and communities, and progress into more advanced topics like developing ethical guidelines, creating inclusive policies, and addressing global AI challenges.<br> By the end of the course, you will have a solid understanding of the ethical and policy-related issues in AI, and the skills to contribute to responsible AI development and governance.<br>  This course is ideal for professionals, policymakers, and anyone interested in understanding the ethical and policy dimensions of AI and ensuring that AI technologies are developed and used in a responsible and equitable manner.<br>', 'AI_Ethics.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/aGwYtUzMQUk', 'AI'),
(24, 'Robotics and AI', 500, 'Dr. Thomas Harris', '2024-10-05', '6 Weeks', 'Explore the integration of AI in robotics and automation.', 'This course provides a comprehensive introduction to Robotics and AI, focusing on the integration of artificial intelligence with robotics to create intelligent and autonomous systems.<br> You will learn key topics, including robotics fundamentals, AI algorithms, sensor integration, machine learning for robotics, and autonomous navigation.<br> The course also covers advanced topics such as robotics simulation, reinforcement learning for robot control, and real-world applications in industries like manufacturing, healthcare, and autonomous vehicles.<br>  The course is structured into modules that start with the basics of robotics and AI, including understanding robotic systems and AI concepts, and progress into more advanced topics like building and programming robots, using AI for perception and decision-making, and optimizing robot performance.<br> By the end of the course, you will have hands-on experience with designing, programming, and deploying robotic systems integrated with AI, as well as understanding how these technologies can solve complex real-world problems.<br>', 'Robotics_and_AI.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/yCXm5cgG0UA', 'AI'),
